Question 1

The final score of the World Cup finals of football is France 4 and Croatia 2. Please use a control structure to print the results as Team - Wins .

wins <- c(4,2)

  print(sprintf("Team %s wins %d",country[i],wins[i]))
}

Question 3

Write a function to get the percentage of NAs in each column.

data <- read.csv("C:/Users/Lenovo PC/Downloads/cat.csv")
library(dplyr)
Percent_Col_NA <- function(x){
  num<-nrow(x)
  percent<-(colSums(is.na(x))/num)*100
  return(percent)
}
data<-data %>% na_if("#N/A")
Percent_Col_NA(data)

Question 4

Write a function to get the percentage of NAs in each row.

# data <- read.csv("C:/Users/Lenovo PC/Downloads/cat.csv")
# library(dplyr)
Percent_Row_NA <- function(x){
  num<-ncol(x)
  percent<-(rowSums(is.na(x))/num)*100
  return(percent)
}
# data<-data %>% na_if("#N/A")

Question 5

Write a function to get a summary of numeric columns (use the summary function) such as THC, CO, CO2, and so on in the data set. With the same function, try to generate box plot using base R.

# Converting to numeric
for (i in c(23:27,29:31)){
  data[,i]<- as.numeric(data[,i])
}

#summary
name<-colnames(data)
numeric_summary <- function(x){
  for (i in 1:ncol(x)){
    if (is.numeric(x[,i])==TRUE){
      print(name[i])
      print(summary(x[,i]))
      print(boxplot(x[,i],main = name[i],horizontal = TRUE))
    }
  }
}
numeric_summary(data)

Question 6

Write a function to create histograms of numeric columns, such as THC, CO, CO2, and so on in the data set. Use ggplot2 to generate figures.

library(ggplot2)
library(dplyr)
generate_histogram<- function(x){
  data1 <- x %>% select_if(is.numeric)
  for (i in 1:ncol(data1)){
    print(ggplot(data.frame(data1[,i]),aes(data1[,i]))+geom_histogram(stat="bin")+xlab(name[i]))
  }
}
generate_histogram(data)

Question 10

Create a new column age based on the date of birth column and the first FD column. Date format is necessary to do basic arithmetic.

library(lubridate)
data7to10$Date.of.Birth <- as.Date(data7to10$Date.of.Birth,"%d/%m/%Y") #Converting to Date class
#DoB can't be greater than 2021 as of now
#as.Date adds 20 before any 2 digit year 00-68 and 19 before 69-99
#Loop for correcting that in DoB
for (i in 1:831){
  if (is.na(year(data7to10$Date.of.Birth[i]))==FALSE  && year(data7to10$Date.of.Birth[i]) > 2021){
    year(data7to10$Date.of.Birth[i]) = year(data7to10$Date.of.Birth[i])-100
  }
}
